[This article clearly indicates that the disease has spread to another county. Much of this article seems to focus on new regulations, such as fencing, and bills to eliminate farmed deer (cevids) and a need for more/better testing.

For years, actually decades, there has been a need to have a live animal test. Currently, there is an immunohistochemistry test for live deer at the Texas Veterinary Medical Diagnostic Laboratory. One wonders why other labs are not partnering with this lab to learn the method and have regulatory agencies approve it. While new methods are always needed, this would be one way to start the process.

Perhaps it is time to consider that the causative agent may not be a prion, as has been touted for decades, but may be another cause. Perhaps research should look in other directions to identify whether there is another cause of this disease. - Mod.TG

HealthMap/ProMED map available at:
Minnesota, United States: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6364182,354]
